§‡à¦•à§‡ à§§à§« à¦•à¦¿à¦²à§‹à¦®à¦¿à¦Ÿà¦¾à¦° à¦¦à¦•à§à¦·à¦¿à¦¨à§‡ à¦¸à§‹à¦¨à¦¾à¦°à¦šà¦°à§‡à¦° à¦‡à¦•à§‹à¦ªà¦¾à¦°à§à¦•à¥¤ à¦ à¦¸à§œà¦•à§‡à¦° à¦¨à¦¿à¦°à§à¦®à¦¾à¦¨ à¦•à¦¾à¦œ à¦à¦–à¦¨à¦“ à¦¶à§‡à¦· à¦¹à§Ÿà¦¨à¦¿à¥¤ à¦¦à§‡à¦¶à§‡à¦° à¦¬à¦¿à¦­à¦¿à¦¨à§à¦¨ à¦ªà§à¦°à¦¾à¦¨à§à¦¤ à¦¥à§‡à¦•à§‡ à¦¨à¦¦à§€à¦ªà¦¥à§‡ à¦ªà¦¾à§Ÿà¦°à¦¾,à¦¬à¦¿à¦·à¦–à¦¾à¦²à§€,à¦“ à¦¬à¦²à§‡à¦¶à§à¦¬à¦° à¦¨à¦¦à§€à¦° à¦¬à¦™à§à¦—à§‹à¦ªà¦¸à¦¾à¦—à¦°à§‡à¦° à¦®à§‹à¦¹à¦¨à¦¾ à¦¦à¦¿à§Ÿà§‡ à¦¯à¦¾à¦“à¦¯à¦¾ à¦¯à¦¾à¦¬à§‡ à¦ à¦¸à§‹à¦¨à¦¾à¦°à¦šà¦°à§‡à¥¤</p>\r\n', '<h3>Sonar Chor Eco Park</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Sonar Chor Sea Beach and Sonar Chor Mangrove Forest. Sonakata / Sonar Chor tourist center has become popular in a few days due to the opportunity to see beaches, mangrove forests and various wildlife.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Sonarchar is the name of this char, which rises in the southern part of Tengragiri Fatra forest of Sonakata union in the southernmost part of Taltali upazila of Barguna district. Locally this forest is known as Fatra forest. Which is spread over 13 thousand acres. This Sonarchar is divided on the south and west by the Bay of Bengal, on the east by the estuary of the Nilganj river and on the north by canals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A wonderful combination of forest and sea has taken place in this golden char. Countless tourists come from different parts of the country during the winter season for leisure. The eco-park of Sonar Char became famous for their walks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At this char, the golden glow of the sunset causes golden scattering in the forest trees. Those who have once enjoyed the beauty of Sonarchar come there again and again, ignoring hundreds of obstacles. There are different types of forest trees in this forest created by the natural and forest department.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Among the trees are Sundari, Gewa, Gani, Keora, Singra, Hetal and Teak. There are various kinds of wild animals in this green forest. Among them are foxes, monkeys, bears, beji, squirrels, wild cats and wild cats.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The chirping of different species of birds on the branches brings unearthly joy to the minds of the tourists. The crocodile has set up a crocodile breeding center in a sweet pond in the forest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tourists are fascinated when they see these animals in the ecopark. It takes about 5/6 hours to see the beauty of the whole ecopark including the various animals that have been released in the ecopark.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You have to walk along the paved road that runs through the ecopark to the beach. Where you can see the huge beach.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At high tide, the green belt sinks 6/7 feet under water. The result is an unprecedented natural scene. This beach offers safe bathing, sunrise and sunset from the same place with sun bath. It is possible to travel by sea from this beach.<br />\r\nHow to get there?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sonarchar Ecopark 15 km south of Taltoli. The construction work of this road has not been completed yet. Sonarchar can be reached by river from different parts of the country through the Bay of Bengal estuary of Payra, Bishkhali and Baleshwar rivers.</p>\r\n', 4, 29, 'sonarchor.jpg', '63.-sonar-chor-sunset1-626x365.jpg', 'sonarchor1-1303650620.jpg', '', '', '', '', 1272, 0, '2022-06-29 11:49:16', 0, 1),
