à§à¦ªà§‡à¦° à¦¸à¦¾à¦¥à§‡ à¦†à¦§à§à¦¨à¦¿à¦• à¦•à¦¾à¦°à¦¿à¦—à¦°à¦¿à¦¬à¦¿à¦¦à§à¦¯à¦¾à¦° à¦®à¦¿à¦¶à§à¦°à¦¿à¦¤ à¦°à§€à¦¤à¦¿ à¦à¦¬à¦‚ à¦®à§à¦—à¦² à¦•à¦¾à¦ à¦¾à¦®à§‹à¦° à¦†à¦¨à§à¦•à§‚à¦²à§à¦¯ à¦¯à¦¾ à¦–à¦¿à¦²à¦¾à¦¨ à¦“ à¦—à¦®à§à¦¬à§à¦œà§‡ à¦¬à¦¿à¦§à§ƒà¦¤, à¦¸à¦®à§à¦­à¦¬à¦¤ à¦ªà¦¾à¦¶à§à¦šà¦¾à¦¤à§à¦¯ à¦¥à§‡à¦•à§‡ à¦‡à¦¸à¦²à¦¾à¦®à¦¿à¦• à¦¸à§à¦¥à¦¾à¦ªà¦¤à§à¦¯ à¦œà¦—à¦¤à§‡ à¦ªà§à¦°à¦¬à§‡à¦¶ à¦•à¦°à§‡à¦›à§‡à¥¤</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>à¦¯à§‡à¦­à¦¾à¦¬à§‡ à¦¯à¦¾à¦¬à§‡à¦¨ &ndash;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>à¦¢à¦¾à¦•à¦¾à¦° à¦—à§à¦²à¦¿à¦¸à§à¦¤à¦¾à¦¨ à¦…à¦¥à¦¬à¦¾ à¦¶à¦¾à¦¹à¦¾à¦¬à¦¾à¦— à¦¹à¦¤à§‡ à¦°à¦¿à¦•à¦¶à¦¾ à¦•à¦°à§‡ à¦–à§à¦¬ à¦¸à¦¹à¦œà§‡à¦‡ à¦•à¦¾à¦°à§à¦œà¦¨ à¦¹à¦² à¦¯à¦¾à¦“à§Ÿà¦¾ à¦¯à¦¾à¦¬à§‡à¥¤</p>\r\n', '<p>When we think of Dhaka University, a few pictures float before our eyes. One of them is Curzon Hall. Not only that, Curzon Hall is a historical and recognized antiquity in Dhaka, the capital of Bangladesh. Witnessing many histories, Curzon Hall is currently being used as a classroom and examination hall for some of the science and biology molecules of Dhaka University.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The foundation stone was laid on February 14, 1904 by George Curzon, then Viceroy and Governor General of India. And the building is named after him, Curzon Hall. The following year, in 1005, Bengal was divided and Dhaka became the capital of the new province of East Bengal and Assam.<br />\r\nWhen the Partition of Bengal was canceled in 1911, it came to be used as a Dhaka College building. Later, when Dhaka University was established in 1921, the building started to be used as part of the science department of the university and is still in use today.&nbsp;There is a huge central hall in this two-storey brick building built in a spacious garden built with great care. Along with it there are attached structures on both the east and west sides which are rich in innumerable rooms and surrounded by a verandah.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Curzon Hall&#39;s exterior is red. In front of the building is a spacious garden, with a road running from west to east through the green chest. Behind it is a huge pond on the west bank of which is the main building of Sher-e-Bangla Fazlul Haque Hall. The two-storey building is considered as one of the best architecture in Dhaka.According to the architects, the architectural design of the building is similar to that of the Fatehpur Sikri fort built by Emperor Akbar. At present, the Curzon Hall building is used for academic purposes of Dhaka University, but it is also one of the entertainment centers for students and tourists from home and abroad. Every afternoon, thousands of people from the university and thousands of people from home and abroad gather here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Considered as one of the best architectures of Dhaka, this building combines a beautiful combination of European and Mughal architectural styles. This is especially noticeable between the protruding north-facing equestrian and grooved arches.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The mix of traditional art with modern craftsmanship and the adaptation of Mughal structures that are embedded in arches and domes have probably entered the world of Islamic architecture from the West.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How to go -<br />\r\nCurzon Hall can be easily reached by rickshaw from Gulistan or Shahbag in Dhaka.</p>\r\n', 1, 1, 'Karjon-Hall.jpg', 'Curzon-Hall-Dhaka.jpg', 'curzon-hall-02.jpg', '', '', '', '', 342, 0, '2022-06-24 04:30:23', 0, 0),
