de of the river Buriganga in Keraniganj upazila of old Dhaka. Jajira is a corruption of the word jinjira meaning island. In 1820, Subedar Ibrahim Khan II built Jinjira Palace as a recreation center. The palace is named Jinjira or the palace of the island because of the surrounding water or jinjira.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A wooden pool was used to get to the beautifully decorated Jinjira Palace, surrounded by the shade of native trees. It is said that after the defeat at the battle of Palashi, Sirajdaula&#39;s family was sent to Jinjira Palace. According to locals, a tunnel was built through the bottom of the Buriganga to communicate with the Lalbagh fort at Jinjira Palace, and this tunnel was used by the Mughal army officers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At present, the entrance arch of the Jinjira Palace, built in the style of a large katra, and two palaces survive. The once desolate village or Haveli has now become a dense settlement. Buildings and shops have sprung up around the Jinjira Palace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How to go</strong><br />\r\nThere are buses, trains, planes, launches etc. from all the districts of Bangladesh to reach the capital Dhaka.&nbsp;From Gulistan in Dhaka to Sadarghat, cross the river Buriganga and reach Bara Katra near Soarighat. If you ask any local, Jinjira will find the palace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Where to stay</strong><br />\r\nThere are more or less residential hotels in almost every area of â€‹â€‹the capital Dhaka. Here you will also find standard hotels starting from 5 star quality hotels. Among the 5 star hotels, Pan Pacific Sonargaon, Hotel La Meridien, Radisson Blu Water Garden etc. are notable. Besides, there are numerous low cost residential hotels in Bangabandhu Avenue, Fakirapul, Paltan, Gulistan and Old Dhaka.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Where to eat</strong><br />\r\nAs you come to the old Dhaka area, you can taste the delicious Biryani on the famous Kazi Alauddin Road, the Pesto Almond Sharbat at Hotel Royal, Nannar Rooster Polao on Becharam Deuri Road, Mohan Mia Juice with Lalbagh Shahi Mosque and Hanif&#39;s Tehri.</p>\r\n', 1, 1, 'Zinzira-Palace-Dhaka-770x420.jpg', 'download.jpg', '', '', '', '', '', 348, 0, '2022-07-01 06:16:22', 0, 0),
