¶à¦¨à§€à¦¯à¦¼ à¦¸à§à¦¥à¦¾à¦¨</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>à¦¸à§‹à¦¨à¦¾à¦•à¦¾à¦Ÿà¦¾à¦° à¦•à¦¾à¦›à§‡ à¦…à¦¬à¦¸à§à¦¥à¦¿à¦¤ à¦†à¦¶à¦¾à¦° à¦šà¦° à¦“ à¦¤à¦¾à¦²à¦¤à¦²à§€ à¦°à¦¾à¦–à¦¾à¦‡à¦¨ à¦ªà¦²à§à¦²à§€ à¦˜à§à¦°à§‡ à¦†à¦¸à¦¤à§‡ à¦ªà¦¾à¦°à§‡à¦¨à¥¤ à¦à¦›à¦¾à¦¡à¦¼à¦¾ à¦¬à¦°à¦—à§à¦¨à¦¾à¦¤à§‡ à¦¶à§à¦­à¦¸à¦¨à§à¦§à§à¦¯à¦¾ à¦¸à¦®à§à¦¦à§à¦° à¦¸à§ˆà¦•à¦¤, à¦²à¦¾à¦²à¦¦à¦¿à¦¯à¦¼à¦¾ à¦¬à¦¨ à¦“ à¦¸à¦®à§à¦¦à§à¦° à¦¸à§ˆà¦•à¦¤, à¦¹à¦°à¦¿à¦£à¦˜à¦¾à¦Ÿà¦¾ à¦ªà¦°à§à¦¯à¦Ÿà¦¨ à¦•à§‡à¦¨à§à¦¦à§à¦° à¦“ à¦¬à¦¿à¦¬à¦¿ à¦šà¦¿à¦¨à¦¿ à¦®à¦¸à¦œà¦¿à¦¦à§‡à¦° à¦®à¦¤à§‹ à¦¬à§‡à¦¶à¦•à¦¿à¦›à§ à¦¦à¦°à§à¦¶à¦¨à§€à¦¯à¦¼ à¦¸à§à¦¥à¦¾à¦¨ à¦°à¦¯à¦¼à§‡à¦›à§‡à¥¤</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Tengra Giri Eco Park</strong>, a wildlife sanctuary, has been set up in Sonakata Union, 24 km from Taltoli upazila of Barguna district, covering a large area of â€‹â€‹forest in the Sundarbans. Sonakata beach is another tourist attraction located next to Tengragiri Ecopark. Declared as a protected forest on July 12, 1960, the forest was known to the locals as Fatra Forest / Patharghata Forest / Haringhata Forest, etc., but in 1986 the forest was renamed as Tengragiri Forest. It is the second largest respiratory forest in Bangladesh after the Sundarbans, which is flooded by tides twice a day. Due to the wonderful mixture of saline and sweet soil, this forest is home to innumerable rows of endangered species of trees, animals, birds and reptiles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tengragiri&#39;s lush green mangrove forests, red crabs chirping on the beach, birds chirping and sunset on the last afternoon&#39;s horizon line are sure to captivate any tourist. And that&#39;s why many travel thirsty people come here from far and wide to get lost in the natural beauty and vastness of the sea to avoid the noise of the citizens. Tengragiri forest covers an area of â€‹â€‹about 4046 hectares up to 9 km east-west and 4 km north-south. The forest is bordered by Kuakata to the east, Sundarbans and Harinbaria to the west, Rakhine to the north and the open Bay of Bengal to the south. This naturally formed forest is rich in various respiratory plants including Keora, Garan, Singra, Hetal, Gewa, Ora. There are also freshwater ponds, numerous small canals, forest department rest houses and picnic corners.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tengragiri forest covers an area of â€‹â€‹about 4046 hectares up to 9 km east-west and 4 km north-south. The forest is bordered by Kuakata to the east, Sundarbans and Harinbaria to the west, Rakhine to the north and the open Bay of Bengal to the south. This naturally formed forest is rich in various respiratory plants including Keora, Garan, Singra, Hetal, Gewa, Ora. There are also freshwater ponds, numerous small canals, forest department rest houses and picnic corners. Going south through the deep forest of Tengragiri / Fatra forest, you will see the 4 km long secluded Sonakata beach. Standing on the beach, the beautiful view of sunrise and sunset will fascinate anyone who loves beauty. And if you want, you can enjoy the biodiversity of the deep forest and the waves of the sea by trawler.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sonakata Ecopark Tourism Center has been set up at Sakhina Beet in Tengragiri Forest Reserve under the Ministry of Forests and Environment in the 2011-12 financial year. In addition to a crocodile breeding center, the ecopark will also feature a variety of wildlife such as deer, pigs, cheetahs, pythons, monkeys, rabbits and wild cats. Currently, this forest has been declared as a safe area for vultures.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>How to go</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Barguna can be reached by road and water from Dhaka. You can take a bus from Sayedabad or Gabtali in Dhaka to Taltali in Barguna and from there you can go to Sonakata Ecopark on a motorcycle. Barguna can also be reached by boat from Sadarghat Launch Terminal on the Patuakhali route. After that you can come to Amtali by bus from Barguna and go to Sonakata by motorbike or easybike. There is also a local trawler or reserve from Kuakata to Tengragiri Ecopark / Fatra Forest.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Where to stay</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When you enter the forest, you will see Amtali Forest Rest House. Overnight stay here is subject to permission from the authorities. If necessary, you can contact Hotel Alam, Hotel Bay of Bengal, Hotel Tajbin, Hotel Bashundhara, Hotel Moumita etc. located in Barguna city.<br />\r\nWhere to eat</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are several Bengali food restaurants on Amtali-Taltali-Sonachar Road.<br />\r\nTengragiri Ecopark Travel Alert</p>\r\n', 4, 29, 'Tengra-Giri-Eco-Park-Barguna.jpg', 'ttttt.jpg', '', '', '', '', '', 717, 0, '2022-06-30 20:13:49', 0, 0),
