²à§‡ à¦•à¦¿à¦¶à§‹à¦°à¦—à¦žà§à¦œ à¦¸à¦¦à¦°à§‡ à¦«à¦¿à¦°à§‡ à¦†à¦¸à¦¤à§‡ à¦¹à¦¬à§‡à¥¤ à¦•à¦¿à¦¶à§‹à¦°à¦—à¦žà§à¦œ à¦¸à¦¦à¦°à§‡à¦° à¦¸à§à¦Ÿà§‡à¦¶à¦¨ à¦°à§‹à¦¡ à¦à¦²à¦¾à¦•à¦¾à§Ÿ à¦°à¦¿à¦­à¦¾à¦° à¦­à¦¿à¦‰, à¦—à¦¾à¦‚à¦šà¦¿à¦², à¦¨à¦¿à¦°à¦¾à¦²à¦¾, à¦‰à¦œà¦¾à¦¨à¦­à¦¾à¦Ÿà¦¿, à¦•à§à¦¯à¦¾à¦¸à§‡à¦² à¦¸à¦¾à¦²à¦¾à¦® à¦¨à¦¾à¦®à§‡ à¦¬à§‡à¦¶ à¦•à¦¿à¦›à§ à¦­à¦¾à¦² à¦®à¦¾à¦¨à§‡à¦° à¦†à¦¬à¦¾à¦¸à¦¿à¦• à¦¹à§‹à¦Ÿà§‡à¦² à¦°à§Ÿà§‡à¦›à¥¤ à¦à¦›à¦¾à§œà¦¾ à¦…à¦¨à§à¦®à¦¤à¦¿ à¦¸à¦¾à¦ªà§‡à¦•à§à¦·à§‡ à¦œà§‡à¦²à¦¾ à¦¸à¦¦à¦°à§‡à¦° à¦¸à¦°à¦•à¦¾à¦°à¦¿ à¦¡à¦¾à¦•-à¦¬à¦¾à¦‚à¦²à§‹à¦¤à§‡ à¦¥à¦¾à¦•à¦¤à§‡ à¦ªà¦¾à¦°à¦¬à§‡à¦¨à¥¤</p>\r\n<script data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-2680215667423951\" async src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js\"></script>', '<script data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-2680215667423951\" async src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js\"></script>\r\n<p>Jangalbari Fort is located in Jangalbari village under Karimganj upazila of Kishoreganj district. At present the fort is in ruins. According to legend, Isa Khan captured the fort from Lakshman Singh Hazra after he was defeated by Mansingh in the Eleventh Indus War.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Probably none of Lakshman Hazra Isa Khan was the builder of the fort. Numerous brick fragments and pottery fragments are found outside the fort area, especially in the southern, western and north-western parts of the fort. The instructions obtained were probably in the pre-Muslim period and it was a center of prosperous settlement. However, Isa Khan has several installations inside the fort.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The surroundings of the fort prove that it was round in shape. Deep trenches were dug to the south, west and north and connected to the Narsundha river to the east. The fort site still seems to be an island. There is nothing left of the fort except a few scattered pieces of brick, fragments of pottery and a few low mounds.Isha Khan&#39;s second capital was Jangalbari in Karimganj upazila on the banks of the river Narsunda.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Numerous pieces of bricks and pottery fragments were found outside the fort area. The evidence suggests that the fort was built before the Muslims arrived. However, Isha Khan has several installations inside the fort. There are ruins of his residence. Although the roof collapsed, much of the courtroom still survives. There are still 10-12 rooms in the hotel adjacent to the court. The descendants of Isha Khan renovated a part of Andarmahal and lived there.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The fort still looks like an island. The surrounding water is so deep that even in the dry season it is impossible to cross without a boat. In the evolution of time, the memory of Jangalbari is lost today.</p>\r\n<script data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-2680215667423951\" async src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js\"></script>\r\n<p>The local administration has renovated a Durbar Hall in the Jangalbari fort of Isha Khan and set up a &lsquo;Isha Khan Memorial Museum.&rsquo; But there is nothing intricate about Isha Khan&#39;s memory except a few photographs and Isha Khan&#39;s genealogy. Besides, some memories of Isha branch have been found in Kishoreganj Public Library.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How to go:<br />\r\nBuses leave Kishoreganj every hour from Gulistan [Unshakha Service] from Mohakhali [Kishoreganj Travels, Ananya, Digital Ananya, Egarasindur, Haor Bilas]. Besides, you can reach Kishoreganj by Egarsindur Express from Dhaka Kamalapur Railway Station at 7.30 am and reach Kishoreganj in three hours on holidays. Then seven kilometers bus, auto rickshaw jangalbari.</p>\r\n<script data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-2680215667423951\" async src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js\"></script>\r\n<p><br />\r\nWhere to eat:<br />\r\nThere is no good food in the vicinity of Jangalbari fort. There is a small hotel in Jangalbari Bazaar near the fort. If you want, you will get rice, vegetables and some local food. It is better to go back to Kishoreganj city and eat your favorite food in restaurants like Dhansindri, Cinnamon, Gangchil, Istikutum, Taj, Maasranga etc. If you are crazy about sweets, you can look at Lakshi Narayan Mistanna Bhandare or Madan Gopal of Ekrampur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nAccommodation:<br />\r\nThere is no arrangement to stay in the vicinity of Jangalbari fort. If you want to stay the night, you have to come back to Kishoreganj Sadar. There are several good quality residential hotels called River View, Gangchil, Nirala, Ujanbhati, Castle Salam in the Station Road area of â€‹â€‹Kishoreganj Sadar. Besides, you can stay in the government post office bungalow of the district headquarters subject to permission.</p>\r\n<script data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-2680215667423951\" async src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js\"></script>', 1, 9, 'greenramble.png', 'd823a_e7998a2c7c_long.jpg', '', '', '', '', '', 291, 0, '2022-06-30 09:15:45', 0, 0);

